	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok, I am no expert, so if I happen to post something that turns out to be BS, by all means, others please correct me.&nbsp;&nbsp;But to my knowledge, kiting is when you snare or root a mob and then DOT it or burn it all the while you are running around them w/ SOW if they are snared or medding while they are rooted.  Well, quad-kiting is using this same tactic on four mobs at one time.  The trick is getting them in very close proximity of each other and then using an area effect spell (in case you arent familiar w/ AOE, it is a spell like careless lightning or cascade of hail, hits target and spreads out affecting other targets).  Therefore, you are just kiting 4 mobs at one time.  Not sure how mana efficient it is, but hey, you are getting four kills....hopefully :).  I have yet to try this as I just recently hit 14th, so I'm still trying to master the single kiting techniques.  Anyway hop this helps.  Good luck.<br><br><br>Raulf, 14th druid<br>Bertoxx<br>"Look at my chops, they are sooo sexay!"<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
