	   <tr><td colspan=2>Thats a pretty darn good explanation, heres just a few things I might add, this is taken from an earlier post of mine.<br><br>Quad Kiting is the art ,and it is an art, of Kiting more than 1, up to 4 (hence quad) mob's at same time, keeping them close and using various AOE spells to kill all 4 at same time or reduce them to panicy crits that you can easily kill. <br><br>There are a few posts on this further down the board that give some good information, warning though, 4 at one time is not as easy as it seems, you need to have your stuff together, build up to it by practicing on 2 ,when good at that , move to 3 and so on. Also ask around for good crits to use this on.<br><br>This is generally done at 35th and above, since you dont get decent AOE spells till 34th its not really a good idea till then, my advice is to wait till then.<br>&nbsp;<br>Fiddo Lupineopolus<br>Cazic Thule<br>What do you mean being lazy is no way to live? It's the only thing I'm good at.</td></tr>
